==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metaphrase
<hw>Met"a*phrase</hw> <pr>(m⟦ecr⟧t"⟦adot⟧*fr⟦amac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>meta`frasis</grk>, from <grk>metafra`zein</grk> to
paraphrase; <grk>meta`</grk> beyond, over + <grk>fra`zein</grk> to
speak: cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧taphrase</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
verbal translation; a version or translation from one language into
another, word for word; a literal translation; -- opposed to
<contr>paraphrase</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An answering phrase; repartee.</def> <rj><au>Mrs.
Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 918 --></p>

<p><ent>metaphrased</ent>⟦br⟧
